3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a computational method for spiking neural networks to emit desired spike trains with precise firing time. This category is also a possible fit for the paper.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes an online regulative mechanism for spiking neural networks based on biological neuronal synapses. This category is a possible fit for the paper.
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - Although less likely, this category could also be a fit for the paper as it deals with the computational complexity of the proposed algorithm.
